column59: Behaviour description
dog sat and waited, looked away once
Attempted to get the kong as soon as handler had it in her hands, sat very fixated on kong, jumping up at handler toward end, and very eager throughout the concentration phase
took a while to sit, then stands, then dog walks away eventually towards the end for a little while handler encourages back with treat
Does lift hindquarters but sits back down without any handler intervention. Stares with profound interest but maintains good composure
lifts hindquarters briefly, yawns, intense start, whine, gets up and explores when he feels like he is not going to be getting it.
initially sniffed around until dog realised that handler had a kong, then sat, stood and eventually jumped at handler x 3
Whining and doesnt break sit but does nudge forward and backward to gain handlers attention
jumped once when handler got given the kong, sat in front then fine, kept looking over briefly, got up and stood beside the handler

Didnt want to sit at first and once he saw the handler had treats was more obsessed with treats, But before that he was definitely heavily enthralled with the kong. No seriously inappropriate behaviour shown
dog sat initially but then walk away, unsure if dog was aware of the stuffed kong, shown again and dog sat and waited for it.
sits
sits calmly
Attention on the kong at times but at other times she is looking around the room. Not overly interested and never broke her sit
sits calmly, looks away briefly twice
Quite consistently lifting hind-quarters and jumps up against handler at the end
Lifts hindquarters a handful of times, but modulates nicely and does not jump up.
dog sits and then goes into a down, keeps looking at handler calmly
sat, then went into a down
Very boisterous and misbehaved jumping up at handler regularly.
broke sit, whined, nudged handler,
Unsettled and jumping up at handler after sitting for a short while
Wanted to jump but modulated well
sits calmly
Does stand from seated position half way through concentration but no inappropriate behaviour - very excited.
dog jumps up at handler once
Whining, jumping up, backing up
sat, went to nudge kong

Excited and activated - regularly lift hind quarters off the floor and changing position. No terrible inappropriate behaviour shown and no jumping up. Didnt notice kong until shown by the handler as she was very distracted by the assessor that had passed with the teddy and/or food etc.
Doesnt jump up but barks and whines.

At first seems partially interested but does turn attention away every now and then. Quickly loses interest, walks away/explores. Handler calls back and the dog gets more interested - higher activation and barking from excitement.
sits calmly
sat
jumps at handler twice
Edging forward, backing up and going side to side. Small jumps on all fours. Doesnt jump up at handler but still overly interested
Very enthralled and jumps out at handler twice
sits, then gives a nudge to the handler
Dog on lead. Anxious behaviour - lip smacking and moving head closer>> maintains sit nicely though
jumps at handler twice
sits and then goes down
sat
sat, jumped up a few times
Sat and then lay down - no inappropriate behaviour at all. Stared very intently at the kong and showed a definite interest.
Very restless - jumps up, backs up, whines and when she thinks shes not getting her way she explores
Moves position and stares intensely
sits and breaks it to move nearer to handler, nudges handler
Jumps up at handler in the beginner - does modulate but I dont think he would have maintained much longer than he did.
sits, jumps at handler, down, sits, down, sits
Edges closer to the handler and sniffs the kong.
Activated, lip smacking, whining, barking, attention seeking, jumping up at handler
sits
sits
sits
Lay down after sitting staring for a while
Jumping up, sitting up on hind quarts (lifts forepaws off the floor), lying down, shifting and restless
Would select n/a if it was here as the kong wasnt really introduced in the normal way, however, the initial reaction was high interest.
sits
sits
activated initially, sits for awhile and then walks away after a while
sitting
sits and jumps up, then sits again
sits and moves slightly forward
sits and moves closer to handler
Lifting hind quarters briefly and fixed staring
some whinging
Sitting and maintaining but not completey into the kong - looking around at the assessors etc.
Sitting and maintaining but stretching head out and staring intently
Sitting calmly. Mostly staring at kong but every now and then he peers over to the rest of the room
sits for a while but doesnt look at the kong at all. Then moves off and explores and doesnt want to come back. No interest.
unsettled, jumping at handler, lying down, whines, sits
sitting
sits, puppy sit, whines, lies down, whines
sitting calmly but occas will look around at any noises heard
stayed sitting, did whine at times
sit moves and resits, jumps up at handler, sits, moves away from handler, jumps up x 2, sits
stayed sitting, only looking away briefly at times usually when she heard something
sits looking intensely at the kong
sits, lies down, sits, whines
sit, stands, whines, moves around
mainly sit and intermittently whines, moves and sits again
stays sitting
sits, moves slightly nearer the handler, whines and sits again
stood beside the handler, occasionally looking around
moves away from handler sniffing around room
sits, then stands then walks away from handler
sits, stands, jumps toward the kong, whines and short bark
sit, jumps at handler and moves around and jumps again on second video dog sits still
sits, stands, whines, sits
Sitting patiently looking over at handler every now and then
stays sitting
sits and then jumps up slightly
Constantly jumping up and barking for trainer to give over the toy. Also walks around the handler in high anticipation.
seated most of the time staring intently at handler in anticipation
sitting and staring at handler in anticipation
Shifting from a sit to a down in order to get attention and perhaps to be rewarded with the kong.
Overly excited to start but loses interest quickly
Goes from jumping to sitting and lying down, always staring intently in anticipation.
Whining, jumping restless and walking around handler constantly
Has no interest in the kong and walks away - highly activated and stressed. Explores and even leaves the testing area again.
No interest at all - he leaves handler to explore
Sitting but shifting position, moving and staring intently
Sitting, shifting closer to handler, continuous barking, lying down, standing up.
